import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='X', y='Y', hue='Series', palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Series')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of X?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['Y'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Y?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['X'])
    mean_x = data['X'].mean()
    std_x = data['X'].std()
    plt.axvline(mean_x, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {mean_x:.2f}')
    plt.axvline(mean_x - std_x, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'STD Lower: {mean_x - std_x:.2f}')
    plt.axvline(mean_x + std_x, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'STD Upper: {mean_x + std_x:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['Y'])
    mean_y = data['Y'].mean()
    std_y = data['Y'].std()
    
    plt.axhline(mean_y, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {mean_y:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(mean_y + std_y, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'+1 Std: {mean_y + std_y:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(mean_y - std_y, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'-1 Std: {mean_y - std_y:.2f}')
    
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
